The paper discusses a real-time optimal trajectory generation method for serial manipulators in dynamic environments, which falls under the field of robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The method is based on machine learning, which involves training models on data, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multiple criteria to evaluate the performance of the models, which falls under the field of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions motion planning for haptic feedback manipulators in virtual reality systems, which involves computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the method for continuous trajectory planning for high-DOF-robots in complex environments, which falls under the field of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely sub-category.
